Column2: Genome Diversity by Ancestry Over Time
description: This dataset tracks the diversity of populations represented in genome-wide association studies (GWAS) over time. It shows the historical trend in the representation of different ancestry groups in genetic research, highlighting both progress and gaps in population diversity. The data is collected from published GWAS studies in the GWAS Catalog, providing insights into the evolution of genetic research inclusivity.
citation: Buniello, A., MacArthur, J.A.L., Cerezo, M. et al.
